headlines.description: — Cade Cunningham hit four free throws in the final 46 seconds to lead the Detroit Pistons to a 106-103 victory over the Cleveland Cavaliers on Thursday night in the teams' return from the All-Star break.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cunningham's late free throws lead Pistons over Cavaliers

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum swooped in and slammed down a dunk for the game's highlight, though he was hardly the only Boston player who didn’t find much resistance from the Nets’ defense on this night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 30 as Celtics romp again in Brooklyn, 129-106

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan made enough big shots down the stretch to keep his record run going and Chicago's winning streak intact.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan continues streak with 37 points, Bulls beat Hawks

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns was on the Minnesota bench for half of the fourth quarter with five fouls. Anthony Edwards was having a way-off night with the ball.
headlines.shortLinkText: Russell scores 37, leads T-wolves past Grizzlies 119-114

events.name: Phoenix Suns at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Devin Booker had 25 points, 12 assists and a career-high six steals to help the NBA-leading Phoenix Suns beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 124-104 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker has 25 points, Suns beat Thunder for 8th straight win

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry had 18 points and 14 assists and the Golden State Warriors returned from the All-Star break to rout the Portland Trail Blazers 132-95 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry, Warriors return from All-Star break to rout Blazers

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 25 points, 12 rebounds and nine assists, Will Barton inched closer to the franchise record for 3-pointers, and the Denver Nuggets beat the Sacramento Kings 128-110 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic, Barton help Nuggets to 128-110 win over Kings
